Wrote a letter to 2022, and it goes a little something like this—

To 2022, I thank you. You gave me the strength and courage I’ve been lacking. The amount of chances, risks, and adventures I took because I wasn’t scared anymore is far more than I ever imagined. You taught me no matter what, life isn’t bad. Everything that has happened to me was all to make me better, more appreciative, softer, wiser. You showed me how important it is to have good people around you. I was able to let my walls down and make new friends, let different people in, be my true authentic self. You helped me say goodbye. I have a heart full of memories that I’ll cherish for a lifetime, but it was time to put it all away and leave it all behind. You brought me a wonderful person I wasn’t looking for. Someone I didn’t know I wanted or needed. You allowed me to accept that I wasn’t hard to love and that I had been being incredibly hard on myself. And with all of that, you brought me to the beautiful, peaceful, exciting new place in my life that I cannot wait to explore. Without you, 2022, I wouldn’t be so ready for 2023. So with that being said…2023; I’ve been ready for a year like you for a very long time. This 28th trip around the sun is about to be filled with love, exhilaration, growth, freshness, and forgiveness to myself for taking so long to get here.

Now let’s do this damn thing, 2023. 🤍
